    "UI Design Draft": "The UI consists of two main sections: a registration panel on the left and a queue dashboard on the right. The registration panel has input fields for patient name and symptoms, plus a 'Register' button. Upon submission, the system calculates urgency and adds the patient. The queue dashboard is a scrollable list showing each patient's name, urgency level (color-coded: red for 1, orange for 2, yellow for 3, green for 4, blue for 5), and waiting time (mm:ss format). At the top of the queue, a 'Take Next Patient' button is available for physicians. The dashboard auto-refreshes every second. The overall style is clean, high-contrast, and optimized for quick scanning.",
    "Anything UNCLEAR": "The requirements do not specify whether multiple physicians can take patients concurrently, how re-triage is performed (e.g., UI for changing urgency), or if there is a need for patient history or audit logs. Also, the system's deployment environment (web vs. desktop) and data storage (in-memory vs. database) are not defined. These details should be clarified with stakeholders."
}
