    "Requirement Analysis": "The system must support real-time queue ordering with a clear tie-breaking rule (urgency descending, then arrival time ascending). It needs a registration interface for nurses, a dashboard view for all clinical staff, and a safe dequeue operation for physicians. The urgency assignment should be algorithmic based on symptom mapping (e.g., ESI protocol) but allow manual override by triage nurse. The data model must handle concurrent updates (arrival, re-triage, removal) without corruption. Persistence should be lightweight (e.g., SQLite or in-memory) for proof-of-concept, but the architecture should allow scaling to a production DB. The dashboard should auto-refresh with sub-second latency.",
